1
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:07,150
The first on-island date.

2
00:00:07,150 --> 00:00:08,332
3 pairs

3
00:00:08,343 --> 00:00:10,310
(Rooftop Sunset: Yang Tinghong)
for 12 islanders.

4
00:00:10,310 --> 00:00:12,520
Did you sit next to me
on purpose yesterday?

5
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:13,310
I really like you.

6
00:00:13,310 --> 00:00:14,920
I took the bold step to go after you.

7
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:17,710
Can you accept someone's flaws
no matter what they are?

8
00:00:17,721 --> 00:00:18,998
As long as they're not extreme.

9
00:00:19,009 --> 00:00:20,840
I think personalities
are not that big a deal.

10
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,083
I'm not that extreme, right?

11
00:00:22,094 --> 00:00:23,763
You seem pretty strong
on possessiveness.

12
00:00:23,823 --> 00:00:25,520
Were you all sincere when you voted?

13
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:26,390
Weren't you?

14
00:00:26,390 --> 00:00:27,710
What did you base your vote on?

15
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,390
Don't play guessing games with me.

16
00:00:29,390 --> 00:00:30,440
No, I'm not.

17
00:00:31,460 --> 00:00:36,460
=Live and Love S2=
=We're on Balance Island=

18
00:00:47,493 --> 00:00:49,000
You went abroad right after undergrad?

19
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:50,150
Yeah.

20
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:51,200
But I didn't finish it.

21
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:52,430
I studied abroad for a year.

22
00:00:52,430 --> 00:00:53,830
I came back when the pandemic hit.

23
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:55,750
So, you finished your studies back home?

24
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:57,000
Yeah, I finished them here.

25
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,000
And after I graduated...

26
00:00:58,520 --> 00:01:00,150
You went overseas again for grad school?

27
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:02,180
Do I really look like someone
who is so educated?

28
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:06,160
So, you did grad school?

29
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,000
Or you just planned to?

30
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:09,910
Nope.

31
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:10,790
You didn't go for it?

32
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:13,870
You seem

33
00:01:13,870 --> 00:01:15,160
like the hardworking type.

34
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:16,830
Thanks.

35
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,590
So, you finished your undergrad,

36
00:01:21,590 --> 00:01:22,230
right?

37
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:24,040
You didn't do graduate school?

38
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:24,800
No.

39
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:25,590
So,

40
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:26,950
I guess you guys are all older

41
00:01:26,950 --> 00:01:27,950
than me.

42
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:29,000
Older than me.

43
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,000
Are you sure?

44
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,790
(Is that right)
I think you're older than me?

45
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,210
No.

46
00:01:33,210 --> 00:01:34,000
I didn't mean that.

47
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:34,660
(I need comfort)

48
00:01:36,310 --> 00:01:37,680
That's not what I meant.

49
00:01:38,270 --> 00:01:38,760
Come on.

50
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:39,350
Tonight,

51
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:41,040
I'll handle him for you
when we get back.

52
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:41,870
What's going on?

53
00:01:42,190 --> 00:01:44,112
(I didn't mean that)
That's not what I meant.

54
00:01:44,123 --> 00:01:45,570
He probably didn't mean it that way.

55
00:01:45,583 --> 00:01:46,960
But it came out sounding like that.

56
00:01:46,971 --> 00:01:47,830
(Help explain)
Yeah.

57
00:01:47,860 --> 00:01:49,190
He's pretty straightforward.

58
00:01:49,190 --> 00:01:49,860
He's not the type

59
00:01:49,963 --> 00:01:51,190
to sweet-talk.

60
00:01:53,980 --> 00:01:56,340
(After the Water Arena match)

61
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:57,040
You're here.

62
00:01:57,630 --> 00:01:58,760
Feeling any better?

63
00:01:58,870 --> 00:02:00,000
It hurts a lot.

64
00:02:00,830 --> 00:02:02,190
Well.

65
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:03,600
You've made it possible for me.

66
00:02:03,611 --> 00:02:04,590
No, no.

67
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,330
You worked for it.

68
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:06,440
It's the same for everyone.

69
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:07,480
No, seriously.

70
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:09,960
I think you should...

71
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,910
Talk to her (Liu Jiayi).

72
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:11,190
Yeah.

73
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:11,830
Open up to her.

74
00:02:11,830 --> 00:02:13,080
I think

75
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,670
you should show how you feel.

76
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:20,110
I think I...

77
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,110
I reached out to her (Liu Jiayi).

78
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,750
That's a pretty big gesture.

79
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:26,750
Then maybe talk with her.

80
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,160
I just want to talk to her

81
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,800
and see what kind of person

82
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:32,110
she really is.

83
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:33,880
Are you picking two or just one?

84
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,670
Well.

85
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:37,320
You can't tell me?

86
00:02:37,830 --> 00:02:39,360
You'll have to wait and see.

87
00:02:41,550 --> 00:02:42,750
I'm really curious.

88
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:44,750
What's your ideal type like?

89
00:02:45,630 --> 00:02:47,720
Someone who doesn't get too emotional.

90
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:50,120
We can talk things out calmly
when something comes up.

91
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:50,420
Right?

92
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,630
When you're in a relationship,

93
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:52,810
you'll definitely have

94
00:02:52,810 --> 00:02:53,800
disagreements sometimes.

95
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:54,240
Yeah.

96
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,550
I've always believed

97
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,570
constant arguing
just wears down the relationship.

98
00:02:57,570 --> 00:02:57,910
Exactly.

99
00:02:57,910 --> 00:02:58,910
If you fight too often,

100
00:02:58,910 --> 00:03:00,440
it definitely hurts the bond.

101
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:01,240
Yeah.

102
00:03:01,670 --> 00:03:03,600
Yesterday,
I gave Zhan Jiaming two votes.

103
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,750
I gave two votes

104
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:05,880
because I wanted

105
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:06,930
to have a chat with her

106
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:08,303
and see what kind of person she is.

107
00:03:08,356 --> 00:03:09,665
She didn't give you that chance?

108
00:03:09,676 --> 00:03:10,285
To talk, right?

109
00:03:10,296 --> 00:03:11,160
She just ignored me.

110
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:11,900
Seriously?

111
00:03:12,190 --> 00:03:14,470
So tonight, will you still vote

112
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:15,243
for her?

113
00:03:15,254 --> 00:03:17,081
I'll wait and see
who I get a date with later.

114
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:18,490
The first place

115
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:20,390
in boys and girls

116
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:22,520
will surely get an advantage.

117
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,270
Congrats to you

118
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:26,750
(On-island Date Arrangement)
on winning the game.

119
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:28,750
You get to choose three pairs

120
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,290
(Rooftop Sunset)
for on-island dates.

121
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,420
(Rooftop Sunset)

122
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,720
Do you like watching the sunset?

123
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:36,670
I do.

124
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:39,270
I once went to the seaside alone

125
00:03:39,270 --> 00:03:40,240
and watched the sunset

126
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,110
at five in the morning.

127
00:03:42,110 --> 00:03:42,830
Oh, sunrise.

128
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,520
Are you the perceiving type?

129
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:45,320
Yeah, I am.

130
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,410
You're the perceiving type.

131
00:03:46,410 --> 00:03:46,690
Right.

132
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:47,960
Is it that obvious?

133
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:50,670
Besides me,

134
00:03:50,670 --> 00:03:51,720
have you reached out

135
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:53,390
to other girls?

136
00:03:53,630 --> 00:03:55,440
Have you seen me with anyone else?

137
00:04:00,110 --> 00:04:01,185
Because I feel like

138
00:04:01,196 --> 00:04:03,160
I'm actually pretty passive.

139
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:05,360
Earth sign?

140
00:04:05,371 --> 00:04:05,883
Earth sign.

141
00:04:05,894 --> 00:04:06,123
Yeah.

142
00:04:06,134 --> 00:04:06,470
Exactly.

143
00:04:06,481 --> 00:04:06,830
Passive.

144
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:08,089
You don't take the initiative.

145
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:08,370
Right.

146
00:04:08,370 --> 00:04:09,290
So for me,

147
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,960
when someone treats me kindly,

148
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:12,720
I'll treat them

149
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:14,520
just as kindly.

150
00:04:17,110 --> 00:04:17,880
You were the first

151
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,320
to come and talk to me,

152
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:20,160
so I guess

153
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,480
that's why I feel this way.

154
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:25,350
Yesterday,

155
00:04:25,350 --> 00:04:27,350
did you sit next to me on purpose?

156
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:28,720
Yeah.

157
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,200
Pretty lucky.

158
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:32,920
I usually start out

159
00:04:35,230 --> 00:04:37,320
just being friends

160
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:39,349
and then

161
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,600
(Based on)
try to move forward

162
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,920
based on the friendship.

163
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:45,350
You can get to know her that way.

164
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,130
I don't want

165
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:48,730
to jump into a relationship too easily.

166
00:04:48,730 --> 00:04:50,040
Because if it starts too easily,

167
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,600
it'll probably end just as easily.

168
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,200
So, I think we should

169
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:55,110
take the time
to get to know each other first.

170
00:04:55,110 --> 00:04:55,510
Well.

171
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:57,160
I warm up pretty slowly.

172
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,920
It usually takes me a long time
to open up.

173
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:00,550
How long are we talking about?

174
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,230
Take a wild guess.

175
00:05:02,230 --> 00:05:03,070
Five years?

176
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:04,980
(That long? You're kidding!)

177
00:05:06,350 --> 00:05:07,670
She might've been married

178
00:05:07,670 --> 00:05:08,830
with kids by then.

179
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:10,550
When you've figured things out,

180
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:11,510
you may realize

181
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:12,490
she's not there for you.

182
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,670
It won't be that long.

183
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:18,320
Honestly, I think it should be

184
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,320
around three weeks.

185
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:20,920
Three weeks?

186
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,160
I thought
you were gonna say three years.

187
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,790
(Slow, not still)
That's impossible.

188
00:05:24,790 --> 00:05:26,440
Three months feels way too long.

189
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,160
One month, actually.

190
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,920
One month.

191
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,230
Right.

192
00:05:29,230 --> 00:05:30,750
In that month,

193
00:05:30,750 --> 00:05:31,440
be friends first;

194
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,720
then make it official.

195
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,320
Does that month include

196
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,670
your first meeting?

197
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:36,110
Yeah.

198
00:05:36,110 --> 00:05:36,830
Being friends?

199
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:37,320
Right.

200
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,790
Then, making it official?

201
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:41,600
You call this phase a long one?

202
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:44,349
Because some people might feel

203
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,442
that they'd make a bold move

204
00:05:45,453 --> 00:05:46,200
when they like you.

205
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,000
They'd go after you

206
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,720
and put their feelings out there

207
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,670
and say

208
00:05:50,670 --> 00:05:51,720
they're into you...

209
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:54,200
Before they get to know you.

210
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:55,390
In that situation,

211
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:57,110
there's something I really worry about.

212
00:05:57,516 --> 00:05:58,189
After you say it,

213
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:00,200
if the other person's not interested,

214
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,920
you might not even be able
to stay friends.

215
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:05,760
Because I believe...

216
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,790
If I appreciate who you are,

217
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,600
I'll be friends with you.

218
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,600
Once we do become friends

219
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,040
and spend some time together,

220
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,830
I come to realize

221
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:18,550
there's something going on.

222
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:20,950
Then I'll move forward.

223
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:32,110
(Cliff Terrace)
What do you like to do for fun?

224
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,110
I'd say sports.

225
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:37,600
Cardio and strength work.

226
00:06:38,110 --> 00:06:39,550
When I hit the gym,

227
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,600
I usually train

228
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,880
for about three to four hours.

229
00:06:43,230 --> 00:06:45,070
Three to four hours?

230
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:46,230
Impressive.

231
00:06:46,230 --> 00:06:48,670
Most people only do two hours max.

232
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:50,720
My genetics aren't great

233
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,760
when it comes to building muscle.

234
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,320
I thought you'd say you were good at it.

235
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,320
Not really.

236
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,070
So, I need

237
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:57,830
super intense training.

238
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:00,440
Then you must be really dedicated.

239
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,230
I saw you swimming like lightning today.

240
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:04,110
Did I?

241
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:07,770
We were shocked when we were standing

242
00:07:07,770 --> 00:07:08,760
on the shore.

243
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:09,550
Really?

244
00:07:18,780 --> 00:07:20,060
(Super shocked)

245
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:20,950
Jiaming and I.

246
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:23,230
That's incredible.

247
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,160
(Impressive)
The speed was unreal.

248
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:26,000
For real.

249
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,270
You'll see it for yourself later.

250
00:07:27,270 --> 00:07:28,350
It was seriously wild.

251
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:29,200
That wild?

252
00:07:31,230 --> 00:07:32,480
Then let me ask you something.

253
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,640
In your mind,

254
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:37,760
what would your perfect partner be like?

255
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,720
Perfect?

256
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,320
Hard to say.

257
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,550
Well...

258
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:48,760
Artificial intelligence

259
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:49,920
is perfect.

260
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:51,670
A robot boyfriend.

261
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:53,440
A digital boyfriend.

262
00:07:54,230 --> 00:07:56,200
Honestly, I've never thought

263
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,000
about finding someone

264
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,950
who's perfect.

265
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:03,350
I know I'm not perfect,

266
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,390
and no one else is perfect.

267
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:09,000
So, I go by how it feels.

268
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,480
I don't want him to just tell me

269
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,880
I'm absolutely perfect.

270
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,760
I want him to be someone...

271
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,490
For example,

272
00:08:16,490 --> 00:08:18,920
someone who highlights the good in me

273
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,550
and accepts my flaws.

274
00:08:20,550 --> 00:08:22,270
I think it should work both ways.

275
00:08:22,510 --> 00:08:24,480
Can you accept

276
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,510
all his flaws?

277
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:28,000
Are there some flaws

278
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,790
that...

279
00:08:29,790 --> 00:08:31,350
Generally speaking,

280
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:32,960
it's okay.

281
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:34,770
As long as it's not too extreme,

282
00:08:34,770 --> 00:08:36,700
I think any personality is fine.

283
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:40,400
As long as his behavior isn't weird...

284
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:44,910
Weird?

285
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:47,790
You just can't be weird.

286
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:51,960
If it's within normal range,
it can be adjusted.

287
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,880
Instead of being weird,

288
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:58,200
it's usually more

289
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,400
about being distinctive.

290
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:00,080
They tend to have

291
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:03,760
distinctive traits.

292
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:04,280
Yeah.

293
00:09:04,590 --> 00:09:06,840
I can accept that.

294
